  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Raising Women&apos;s Political Participation in Brazil</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">While women are 51% of the population in Brazil, just 15% of Parliamentarians are women. Supported by CHIME FOR CHANGE, UN Women will host capacity-building convenings to support women leaders as they work towards Brazil 50-50, a parity democracy that will balance the political representation of men and women. Our work will assemble a group of women leaders from Brazil&apos;s political parties, including young, Afro-Brazilian and indigenous women to increase their political participation.</narrative>
  </description>
